<h1>@starlib_pkg_button_style.style_variable</h1>
<p>starlib_pkg_button_style.style_variable performs the role of global.binding, but with using annotation starlib_pkg_button_style.button_style_template.</p>
<div>
    <span class="load-content" data-file="docs/global/binding">@global.binding</span>
    <span class="load-content" data-file="docs/package_button/button_style/button_style_template">@starlib_pkg_button_style.button_style_template</span>
    <div id="important-info-container" class="important-info">
        <div class="important-info-bar"></div>
        <div class="important-info-content">
            <h3>How it works?</h3>
            <p>If $key exists in #form_button_text, texture is visible.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="table-container">
    <table>
        <thead>
            <tr>
                <th>Key</th>
                <th>Default value</th>
                <th>Description</th>
                <th>Type</th>
            </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr>
                <td>$key</td>
                <td>""</td>
                <td>Key to show style element.</td>
                <td>string</td>
            </tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>
</div>
<div class="code-container">
    <div class="code-header">
        <h3>Example</h3>
        <button class="copy-button"></button>
    </div>
    <div class="code-content">
    //...
    "custom_style_variable@starlib_pkg_button_style.style_variable": { //Annotation
        "$key": "green", //Key
        "texture": "textures/my_ui/green_button_style" /*Since style_variable uses
        starlib_pkg_button_style.button_style_template, we can modify it direcly*/
    }
    </div>
</div>